snippet.textDisplay: I think we have to keep things in perspective with these price points... she has to raise the price a bit to compensate for the problems with previous manufacturing issues and the losses from those issues. I appreciate a solid product that I don’t have to worry about fibers, hairs, and a number of various other possible contaminants. I’d rather pay a little more to ensure my safety than get something for less and risk my safety. I trust Marlena and her ethics so I’m more likely to spend the extra money confidently than have buyers remorse. I know everybody is in different financial situations but I’m a strong believer in you get what you pay for. I’d rather save for a few more weeks and get a good product I will love and use than get what I can afford and be unhappy and end up spending more over all because now I have to save for the pallet I really wanted and that was better for me.
